docs.snippet: It’s not just the emergency declaration. President Trump is also siphoning more than $2 billion in military funds for his wall through another complex move.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s plan to spend billions of dollars more on his border wall than Congress approved involves more than his invocation of emergency powers to redirect military construction funds. headline.main: Trump to Tap Other Military Money for Wall Before Emergency Funds

docs.abstract: The Treasury Secretary is pressing China to give American movies greater access, raising conflict of interest concerns given his financial ties to the film industry.
docs.snippet: The Treasury Secretary is pressing China to give American movies greater access, raising conflict of interest concerns given his financial ties to the film industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — “Wonder Woman,” the 2017 film that Steven Mnuchin helped produce before becoming Treasury secretary, hauled in about $90 million at the box office in China. It was the film’s most successful international market and a roaring success for an American superhero export. But because of China’s strict laws for foreign films, the studio behind the movie, Warner Bros., received just a small fraction of those revenues.

headline.main: Mnuchin’s Hollywood Ties Raise Ethical Questions in China Talks
headline.print_headline: Mnuchin’s Hollywood Ties Raise  Ethics Questions in China Talks

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve lowered its growth forecast to 2.1 percent this year, far less rosy than White House projections, as it detected signs of a slowing economy.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve lowered its growth forecast to 2.1 percent this year, far less rosy than White House projections, as it detected signs of a slowing economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve said Wednesday that the United States economy was slowing more than it had previously thought and painted a far less rosy economic picture than the White House as it left interest rates unchanged and signaled little appetite for raising them again in the near future.

headline.main: Fed, Dimming Its Economic Outlook, Predicts No Rate Increases This Year
headline.print_headline: Fed Downgrades Forecast, Leaving Rates Unchanged
